This paper deals with approximation algorithms for a graph traversal problem, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The problem involves visiting all nodes in a metric with a single vehicle, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of LP relaxations and integrality gaps suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of linear programming (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the focus on approximation algorithms and optimization suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of algorithms (cs.AL) or machine learning (cs.LG).
